This paper discusses the development of self-sustainable communications based on advanced energy harvesting technologies, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the optimization of communication performance, which is related to information theory, leading to the possibility of cs.IT (Information Theory) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also introduces analytical models to characterize the impacts of the considered environment factors, which is related to mathematical analysis, leading to the possibility of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the integration of different communication technologies, which is related to control theory, leading to the possibility of cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulations to evaluate the performance of the proposed system, which is related to multimedia, leading to the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fifth likely sub-category.
